text: Netta Barzilai (; born 22 January 1993), sometimes known as simply Netta, is an Israeli singer and artist. Barzilai served in the Israeli Navy and lives in Tel Aviv. In May 2018, she represented Israel at the Eurovision Song Contest 2018 with the song "Toy". She won the competition, marking Israel's fourth win. == Discography == === Albums === * Goody Bag (2020) * The Best of Netta's Voice (2020) === Singles === * Toy (2018) * Bassa Sababa (2019) * Ricki Lake (2020) * Cuckoo (2020) * The Times They Are-a-Changin' (2021) * CEO (2021) * I Love My Nails (2022) * Playground Politica (2022) * Everything (2023) == Filmography == === Film === * Eurovision Song Contest: The Story of Fire Saga (herself) * The Great Hack (Woman singing) === Television (as herself) === * The X Factor Israel (judge) ==Sources== Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Eurovision Song Contest winners Category:Singers from Tel Aviv Category:Actors from Tel Aviv
